"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-nandos-quick-to-react-to-tatjana-smith-gold-medal-from-smith-to-goldsmith-breaking\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbNando's quick to react to Tatjana Smith's gold medal: 'From Smith to Goldsmith'  Chicken fast food chain\\u00a0Nando's was quick to react\\u00a0to Team South Africa's first gold medal at the Paris Olympics 2024 on Monday.  Chicken fast food chainNando'swas quick to react\\u00a0toTeam South Africa'sfirst gold medal at theParis Olympics 2024on Monday.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  Tatjana Smithfinished strong to claim victory in the women's 100m breaststroke at the Paris La Defense Arena.  Smith stopped the clock in a time of1:05:28, finishing ahead of China'sQianting Tang(1:05:54), with Ireland'sMona McSharryin third (1:05.59).  The gold was South Africa'sthirdmedal at this year's Games after bronze medals won by themen's rugby sevensteam andAlan Hatherlyin the men'smountain bike cross country.  Nando's took tosocial mediato post an image with the words \\\"From Smith to Goldsmith\\\".  The tweet was captioned \\\"Guess who ordered gold for takeaway?\\\"  Smith will be the favourite in the women's 200m breaststroke later in the week where she is the reigning Olympic champion having triumphed in Tokyo in 2021.  Smith also pocketedR400 000for her win thanks to the financial incentives promised by theSouth African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc).  Smith's coach, Rocco Meiring, will earn R100 000 for his role's in Smith's victory.  IndividualsGold medallists R400 000 and the coach R100 000Silver medallists R200 000 and the coach R50 000Bronze medallists R75 000 and the coach R25 000  In addition, as reported byThe South African website, new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, promised that he has a 'big surprise' for all Team SA medal winners, suggesting there could be more prize money coming their way.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  Nando's is a South African multinational fast casual chain that specialises in Portuguese flame-grilled peri-peri style chicken.  It was founded in Rosettenville in Johannesburg in 1987 by Portugal-bornFernando Duarteand South Africa-bornRobert Brozin.  Upon visiting a Portuguese-Mozambican\\u00a0takeaway named Chickenland and trying the chicken with peri peri, the pair bought the restaurant for about R80 000.  They renamed the restaurant Nando's after Fernando's first-born son.  Nando's operates over 1 200 outlets in 30 countries.  Their logo depicts the Rooster of Barcelos, one of Portugal's most common symbols.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"